text: Your Wednesday Evening BriefingHere’s what you need to know at the end of the day.
The Modern Love PodcastWelcome to the new season.
Listen to ‘The Daily’Where is this pandemic headed?
Here are six key questions ahead of the debate at 9 p.m. Eastern time.
Mike Pence, Kamala Harris and the debate’s moderator, Susan Page, will not wear masks onstage, but everyone else in the audience will be required to do so.
President Trump is insisting that he is “looking forward” to the next debate. Joe Biden’s team said the president must prove he’s not contagious.
The measures taken to protect Mike Pence, Kamala Harris and others will not prevent airborne transmission, the greatest threat in this setting.
Women and suburbanites continue to power Joe Biden’s support, new Times/Siena polls show. Many voters say campaigning in front of large crowds is inappropriate.
The Justice Department has long sought to avoid public investigations that could disrupt free elections. It is now undoing those rules.

Notre Dame’s President Faces an Angry Campus After Getting the VirusStudents and faculty are furious that the Rev. John Jenkins did not wear a mask at a White House event and then later tested positive for the coronavirus.

Backlash Grows in Orthodox Jewish Areas Over Virus Crackdown by CuomoReligious leaders lashed out at Gov. Andrew Cuomo over new coronavirus restrictions as protests and fires broke out in Brooklyn overnight.
New Zealand Stamps Out the Virus. For a Second Time.Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern, who is facing re-election, called the country’s reopening a validation of its “go hard, go early” response.

“Too little support would lead to a weak recovery, creating unnecessary hardship for households and businesses,” Jerome H. Powell, the Federal Reserve chair, said on Tuesday. Stefani Reynolds/Bloomberg

Analysis: Scuttling Stimulus, Trump Invites Risk for Himself and G.O.P.The president’s abrupt move to upend stimulus negotiations removed any ambiguity about who was responsible for the lack of an aid bill.
Why Conspiracy Theories Are So Addictive Right NowQAnon, #TrumpCovidHoax and other conspiracy theories may be part of a larger authority crisis created by the internet, Kevin Roose writes.
